    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#ensoli1996"/>, pp. <citedRange>81-84</citedRange></bibl> (excavations of the building and mention of the inscription), whence 
                   <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>46.2208</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>110000</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>100</citedRange> (date), p. <citedRange>366</citedRange>, number 90 (text)</bibl>.</p>
                    <p>Cf. S. Ensoli in <bibl><ptr target="#bonacasa-ensoli2000"/>, p. <citedRange>130</citedRange> (restored drawing)</bibl>;
                        a thorough publication by S. Ensoli for the architecture and G. Paci for the inscription is still awaited.
                  </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><milestone unit="block" n="1"/><space quantity="1.65" unit="metre"/>
                        <milestone unit="block" n="2"/><space quantity="0.52" unit="metre"/> <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φιλοθάλης">Φι<supplied reason="lost">λοθά</supplied><milestone unit="block" n="3"/>λη<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἰάσων">Ἰάσονο<milestone unit="block" n="4"/>ς</name></persName></persName> <rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω">ἱαριτεύ<supplied reason="lost">ω
                        <milestone unit="block" n="5"/>ν</supplied></w></rs> <supplied reason="lost">ἀνέθηκε</supplied>
                        <milestone unit="block" n="6"/><space quantity="1.65" unit="metre"/>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#ensoli1996 #IGCyr #rosamilia2023">ἱαριτεύ<supplied reason="lost">ων</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg type="alternative" resp="#IGCyr">ἱαριτεύ<supplied reason="lost">σας</supplied>? <note>(suggested as also possible)</note></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="1"><lem resp="#IGCyr #rosamilia2023"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέθηκε</supplied> <note>(IGCyr in commentary)</note></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#bonacasa-ensoli2000 #IGCyr">Ἀπόλλωνι <note>(IGCyr as alternative in commentary)</note></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Philothalès fils d'Iasôn <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">a consacré</supplied> durant sa prêtrise.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Philothales son of Iason <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">dedicated</supplied> while being priest.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Philothales figlio di Iason <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ha dedicato</supplied> quando era sacerdote.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Some details were given at <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/></bibl> from the features that any visitor to the site might observe. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> 
                    was able to be more precise about the space available on block 4, leading to prefer the present participle and to restore its final <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ν</foreign> 
                    on block 5. The verb of dedication is surely to be restored after that. However, this does not leave at right on block 5 a vacat symmetrical with that on block 2 at left. 
                With the awaited final archaeological publication, this difficulty will probably be solved.</p>
                <p>As noted by <bibl><ptr target="#ensoli1996"/></bibl>, Philothales son of Iason is the priest on duty in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr011400</ref>. He is also mentioned in a fragmentary 
                    list of priests (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr094800</ref>).</p>
                <p>About the first clearance of the Isieion behind the fountain, see <bibl><ptr target="#luni2014a"/>, p. <citedRange>64</citedRange></bibl> and about the discovery of the 
                    inscription <bibl><ptr target="#bartolini2014"/>, pp. <citedRange>111, 115</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div></body>
